### Vite Config & GitHub Pages

#### [MODIFY] [frontend/vite.config.js](file:///E:/Software/CalculateShopeCostSummary/ShopeeWeb/frontend/vite.config.js)
- Remove the `proxy` block (no backend needed)
- Add `base: '/ShopeeWeb/'` (or your GitHub Pages repo path — needs your GitHub repo name)

#### [NEW] [frontend/.gitignore](file:///E:/Software/CalculateShopeCostSummary/ShopeeWeb/frontend/.gitignore) additions
Add entries to protect secrets:
```
.env
.env.local
firebase-import-script/shop-jj-app-firebase-adminsdk-fbsvc-887a2f804e.json
firebase-import-script/node_modules
```

#### [NEW] `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`
GitHub Actions workflow for auto-deploying to GitHub Pages on every push to `main`. Uses `npm run build` and pushes `dist/` to `gh-pages` branch. Requires you to set `VITE_*` environment variables as GitHub Secrets.

---

## Things I Need From You

1. **Your Firebase Web Config** — Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com) → `shop-jj-app` → Project Settings → Your Apps → Web app → Config. Copy the `firebaseConfig` object values.
2. **Your GitHub repo name** — so I can set the correct `base` path in Vite (e.g., `CalculateShopeCostSummary` or `ShopeeWeb`).
3. **The admin password** you want to use for the frontend login.

